swordschool.net/index.php/helsinki-beginners/\">Click here for more information about the course content.</a>\r\n<h3>Helsinki schedule</h3>\r\nOver the Christmas period: class will run as normal on the 19th December, the 30th December, and from January 2nd onwards. We are closed on December 23rd, 24th, 26th, and 31st. If a free scholar chooses to run extra training during this time, it will be announced on <a title=\"SES FB group\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/6336234189/\" target=\"_blank\">our Facebook group</a> page.\r\n<div>\r\n<pre>[timetable id=1 start=\"today\"]</pre>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\nTuesday evening Basic classes will be mostly taught by Class Leaders and those working towards that qualification, usually under the direction of the Instructor. This is to provide opportunities for senior students who wish to teach to learn to do so.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b>Payments</b>\r\n\r\nPayments to the Suomen Historiallisen Miekkailun Seura Ry should go to this account:\r\n\r\nNordea FI53 1015 3000 2149 03\r\n\r\nPlease remember to use your viitenumero, or explain in the message field what it is for.\r\n\r\nIf in any doubt, please ask the treasurer: laura dot husu at gmail dot com\r\n<h3>Classes and Events calendar</h3>\r\n<iframe style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/calendar/embed?src=0n7svv9vc85991i4kntp373vu0%40group.calendar.google.com&amp;ctz=Europe/Helsinki\" height=\"600\" width=\"800\"></iframe>','Helsinki','','inherit','closed','open','','28-revision-v1','','','2013-12-13 11:13:54','2013-12-13 09:13:54','',28,'http://swordschool.com/index.php/28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(444,3,'2013-12-17 11:29:40','2013-12-17 09:29:40','<a href=\"http://swordschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/rapier1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-321\" alt=\"rapier1\" src=\"http://swordschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/rapier1-300x215.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"215\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe seminar will run from 11.00 to 17.00\r\n\r\nAt our Helsinki Salle, Luiskatie 8, 00770 Helsinki\r\n\r\nThe seminar will cost 40€, 30€ for students and unemployed.\r\n\r\nPlaces are limited, so please sign up by email to info@swordschool.com as soon as possible!\r\n\r\nIn a change to the original plan: we will spend the time looking at the most exciting rapier discovery of the century so far: Giganti\'s second book, originally published in 1608 and lost for centuries before being re-discovered in 2012 and published in translation in 2013. You can find out more about this book and its contents <a title=\"about the 1608\" href=\"http://wp.me/p2qLSv-aO\" target=\"_blank\">in this blog post</a>. In this seminar we will work through some of the plays from this book, and compare it to other rapier sources, such as Giganti\'s first book, and of course, Capoferro.\r\n\r\n<em> </em>You can find examples of rapier techniques on our <a href=\"http://www.swordschool.com/wiki/index.php/Rapier\">wiki here</a>, and in our Instructor\'s book on rapier training,<a href=\"http://www.scribd.com/doc/116228480/The-Duellist-s-Companion\"> <em>The Duellist\'s Companion</em></a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>All Welcome!</strong>\r\n\r\nPlaces are limited, so please sign up by email to info@swordschool.com as soon as possible!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Rapier Seminar, February 23rd','','publish','closed','open','','rapier-seminar-february-23rd','','','2014-01-23 13:17:23','2014-01-23 11:17:23','',0,'http://swordschool.com/?p=444',0,'post','',0),(445,3,'2013-05-30 12:06:46','2013-05-30 10:06:46','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-321\" src=\"http://swordschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/rapier1.jpg\" height=\"1507\" width=\"2097\" alt />The next Beginners\' Course in Helsinki will run on Wednesday evenings from September 4th to October 23rd, 2013.\r\n\r\nClasses will run from 18.00 to 19.30\r\n\r\nAt our Helsinki Salle, Luiskatie 8, 00770 Helsinki\r\n\r\nThe course will cost 120e, 100 for students and unemployed.\r\n\r\nPlaces are limited, so please sign up by email to info@swordschool.com as soon as possible!\r\n\r\nThe course will introduce students to the noble art of swordsmanship as laid out for us by Ridolfo Capoferro in 1610, in his book <em>The Great Representation of the Art and Use of Fencing. </em>You can find examples of the techniques on our <a href=\"http://www.swordschool.com/wiki/index.php/Rapier\">wiki here</a>, and in our Instructor\'s book on rapier training,<a href=\"http://www.scribd.com/doc/116228480/The-Duellist-s-Companion\"> <em>The Duellist\'s Companion</em></a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Welcome to the School</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you have never trained with us before, there are a few things you should know.\r\n\r\n1) Beginners are welcome. Every student begins knowing nothing, and we expect to teach you everything from scratch.\r\n\r\n2) You will need only a white t-shirt, dark sports trousers, and indoor training shoes to start with. We can lend you the necessary equipment, such as swords and masks.\r\n\r\n3) Come in time to get changed before class, the salle will be open by 17.30.\r\n\r\nPlaces are limited, so please sign up by email to info@swordschool.com as soon as possible!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Rapier Beginners\' Course: Helsinki, September 4th to Oct 23rd','','inherit','closed','open','','319-revision-v1','','','2013-05-30 12:06:46','2013-05-30 10:06:46','',319,'http://swordschool.com/index.php/319-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(446,3,'2013-12-17 11:27:41','2013-12-17 09:27:41','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-321\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://swordschool.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/rapier1.jpg\" width=\"2097\" height=\"1507\" />The next Beginners\' Course in Helsinki will run on Wednesday evenings from September 4th to October 23rd, 2013.\r\n\r\nThe seminar will run from 11.00 to 17.00\r\n\r\nAt our Helsinki Salle, Luiskatie 8, 00770 Helsinki\r\n\r\nThe seminar will cost 40€, 30€ for students and unemployed.\r\n\r\nPlaces are limited, so please sign up by email to info@swordscho